# name: test_error_message[tuple_index.py]
  '''
  tuple_index.py:4:16: error: a tuple can only be indexed by an integer literal
  
    4 |     print(pair[i])
      |                ^
  
    help: a tuple holds a different type at each position, so the position has to be known at compile time.
            Index it with a literal:
            pair[0]
            or hold the values in a list, where every element has one type:
            pair = [1, 2]
            print(pair[i])
  
  '''
